tions.\nWhat\u2019s become of that friend\nwho borrowed a few dollars from\nyou a month or so ago?\nSTOP THAT ITCH!\nIN JUST 15 MINUTES,\nYour itch MUST stop or your\n48c back at any drug store. Ap\nply ITCH-ME-NOT io deaden\nitch, burning in minutes, speed\nhealing. For externally caused\nitch, get ITCH-ME-NOT today at\nF. P. MAY DRUG CO.\nHAULING\nTRUCKING\nALL KINDS\nand Long Distance\nFurniture Insured\nSam Huiley\nS. ADAMS ST.\nMAin 7-6433\nPAGE THIRTEEN\nMrs. Hancock, RN, To\nAttend Convention\nMrs. Audrey Hancock, R. N.,\nof Quincy, will attend the bien\nnial convention of the American\nNurses Association in Atlantic\nCity June 9-13. Mrs. Hancock\nis a member of District No. 15\nof the Florida Nurses Associa\ntion.\nThe theme of the convention\nis \u201cThe Professional Nurse\nPractioner and Citizen\u201d.\nMore than 10,000 nurses are\nexpected to attend the conven\ntion _\nRIGHT\ng WHERE YOU'D\n3 EXPECT\n9/ IT\nJU TO\nBE\ny ALCOA g.\n^aluminum\nAvailable\nIT\nQuincy rl\nA\nBEU\n\nBATES\nHARDWARE\nCOMPANY\nQuincy","height":"29352","width":"20292"}}
